com.sun.tools.example.trace
Class Trace

java.lang.Object
  com.sun.tools.example.trace.Trace

public class Trace
extends java.lang.Object

This program traces the execution of another program. See "java Trace -help". It is a simple example of the use of the Java Debug Interface.

Version:
Author:
Robert Field Modified for Sequence Diagram 2007 Instituto Politecnico de Beja Escola Superior de Tecnologia e Gestao by Nuno Fortes

Method Detail

generateTrace

void generateTrace(java.io.PrintWriter writer,
                   SD sd,
                   java.lang.String from)
Generate the trace. Enable events, start thread to display events, start threads to forward remote error and output streams, resume the remote VM, wait for the final event, and shutdown.

Parameters:
writer - Device to write to
sd - Sequence Diagram reference
from - class.function to start from, otherwise empty string
